Finding all elements in an array that are smaller than a given number K is a common requirement. This can be efficiently achieved by traversing the array and storing the results in a dynamic data structure, such as an ArrayList.

Examples:

Input: 
arr = [5, 1, 8, 3, 7]
K = 6
Output: [5, 1, 3]

Input: 
arr = [10, 15, 7, 20, 3]
K = 10
Output: [7, 3]

-> Approach
The problem can be approached by following these steps:
a. Create a dynamic list (ArrayList) to store elements smaller than K.
b. Traverse the array and compare each element with K.
c. If the element is smaller than K, add it to the list.
d. Return the resulting list.

-> Implementation
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;
​public class GFG {
​    // Method to find elements smaller than a given value K
    public static List<Integer>
    findSmallerElements(int[] arr, int K)
    {
​
        // Creating a List to store the result
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
​
        for (int num : arr) {
​
            // Check if the current element is smaller than
            // K
            if (num < K) {
​
                // Add the element to the result list
                result.add(num);
            }
        }
​
        return result;
    }
​
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
​
        int[] arr = { 5, 1, 8, 3, 7 };
        int K = 6;
        List<Integer> smallerElements
            = findSmallerElements(arr, K);
        System.out.println("Elements smaller than " + K
                           + ": " + smallerElements);
    }
}

Output
Elements smaller than 6: [5, 1, 3]

-> Alternative Approach: Using Java Streams (Java 8+)
This approach uses Java Streams for a more concise solution:
a. Convert the array into a stream using Arrays.stream().
b. Use the filter() method to keep only elements smaller than K.
c. Convert the filtered elements to a List using boxed() and collect(Collectors.toList()).
e. Return or print the resulting list of smaller elements.

-> Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;
​public class GFG{
​    public static void main(String[] args) {
​        // Initializing the array
        int[] arr = { 5, 1, 8, 3, 7 };
​
        // Value to compare with array elements
        int K = 6;
        List<Integer> smallerElements =
                Arrays.stream(arr)            // Convert array to IntStream
                      .filter(num -> num < K) // Filter elements less than K
                      .boxed()                // Convert int to Integer (autoboxing)
                      .collect(Collectors.toList()); // Collect result into a List
​
        // Printing the result
        System.out.println("Elements smaller than " + K + ": " + smallerElements);
    }
}

Output
Elements smaller than 6: [5, 1, 3]
